    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nThe code that handles item group alignment and truncation contains several bugs that can lead to buffer overflows, mostly related to multibyte or multicell characters. See commit message for details.\r\n\r\nThe most practically relevant bug is that multibyte `fillchars` write over the contents of right-aligned item groups.\r\nFor example:\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean +\"set fillchars+=stl:∙ stl=%5(X%)\"\r\n```\r\nproduces `∙∙∙∙<e2>`, the item group content `X` being lost.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nBe more careful with out-of-bounds checks, use clearer variable names, don't recycle variables for different purposes.",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-13T17:57:02Z",
